SIMPLE: adduction
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Adduction
<hw>Ad*duc"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>adduction</ets>. See <er>Adduce</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
act of adducing or bringing forward.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An <qex>adduction</qex> of facts gathered from various
quarters.</q> <rj><qau>I. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>The action by which the parts
of the body are drawn towards its axis]; -- opposed to
<ant>abduction</ant>.</def> <rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Adductive</ent>⟦br⟧
